forecast.review: Both forecasters reinforced key constraints I partially noted: (1) the blog/news-post path is rare without a public S-1 due to norms around quiet periods; (2) late June/early July is typically a weak window for IPO marketing, with many issuers preferring late summer/early fall; and (3) the resolution source is stricter than a generic press release—Discord’s own news page or an S-1 on EDGAR. The emphasis on the rarity of a pre-S-1 blog announcement and the seasonality argument strengthens the case for lower odds before July 1. I find their reasoning sound and directionally consistent with base rates.
forecast.rationale: There are ~5.5 weeks left. The two qualifying paths are: (a) a public S-1 in June; or (b) a specific IPO announcement on Discord’s news/blog. Given industry practice, (b) is unlikely absent a filing. If Discord targets a fall listing, a public S-1 in July/August (post–July 1) is more typical. While credible reporting and named underwriters imply 2025 intent, that does not tightly couple to a pre–July 1 public S-1. The stricter resolution sources (S-1 or Discord’s own news page) further reduce the chance that a wire-only PR would count. Balancing a feasible but narrow June S-1 window against seasonality and norms, I trim my estimate. I move from 35% to 27%.
